    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="805"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-05T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 5, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>125. Elections were orderly. Decisive majority in favor of Montero assures
                    political quiet for the time being. Alessandri announces that he accepts
                    verdict. Under the Constitution Montero will assume the Presidency on November
                    24th but he may immediately resume executive power which he turned over
                    temporarily as reported in my <pb facs="1032" n="918" xml:id="pg_918"/> telegram
                    96, August 21, 4 p.m. In that case the Cabinet will be reorganized.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Lima and Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
